caption: b'AOA Racing is the current points leader in the World Racing League National Championship. We wish them luck as they head into this weekend\xe2\x80\x99s championship at @cota_official.'
b'It\xe2\x80\x99s the final day to get 30% off any 2020 #MazdaMotorsports merchandise. Use the promo code VICTORY30 at check out. #LinkInBio'

b'Before winning the Mazda MX-5 Cup Shootout, @aaronjracing won the @specmx5 Invitational Championship and the Emerging Talent award, earning an invitation to the shootout and ultimately winning the $110k scholarship prize. #GrassrootsTuesday @mazdausa #MazdaMotorsports'

b'NBC caught up with 2020 Global Mazda #MX5Cup champion @michael_carter08 at Sebring, who spoke about his excitement for @globalmx5cup next year, and his hopes for his future racing career with #MazdaMotorsports. @IMSA_racing @mazdausa'
b'#TBT to the sights of @sebringraceway. There was no better way to cap off the season than a double podium with a #MazdaMotorsports victory. #IMSA'

b'At #MazdaMotorsports, our passion for racing runs deep, and we aim to fuel that passion in others by giving aspiring drivers the resources and mentorship they need to advance their careers. \n\nNow, these talented scholarship winners will be ready to release their #PowerofPotential in 2021.'

b'Congratulations to our #MX5Cup Shootout scholarship winners: Aaron Jeansonne ($110K award), Savanna Little ($75K), and Chris Nunes ($75K), and to the Spec MX-5 Club Racing Factory Team: Bryson Morris and Alex Berg. We look forward to seeing what you can achieve in 2021. #MazdaMotorsports'

b'Nine drivers have been selected to take part in the 2020 Mazda MX-5 Shootout with 10 to compete in the Spec MX-5 Shootout. Today, up to five will earn support from #MazdaMotorsports to advance to the next level in their racing careers.'

b'Looking to celebrate a #MazdaMotorsports victory and show off your #ChallengerSpirit? Enjoy 30% off the entire Mazda Collection now through 11/30. 

Promo Code: VICTORY30
Link in bio.'

b'2020 marks the 15th year of the Mazda MX-5 Shootout. From opening the event to karters, to providing additional support to women in motorsport, this year @MazdaUSA continues to offer defining opportunities for drivers to join #MazdaMotorsports in sports car racing. We wish the best of luck to all competitors.'

b'For 12 grueling hours, our drivers, engineers and crew performed with skill, passion and determination to put 2 Mazdas on the podium and bring home a victory. There\xe2\x80\x99s no better demonstration of @mazdausa\xe2\x80\x99s  #NeverStopChallenging spirit than ending an unconventional 2020 season on this final note.'

b'It\xe2\x80\x99s a #MazdaMotorsports victory!\n\nA win for the #55 of @harrytincknell, Jonathan Bomarito and @ryanhunterreay, and a third place finish for the #77 of @oliverjarvis1, @tristannunez77 and @olivierplaracing.'

b'It will take nothing short of a strong resolve, teamwork and human ingenuity to take on the final race of 2020. #MazdaMotorsports is up for the challenge. \n\nTune in for the #Sebring12 today at 10:00 AM ET on NBC Sports. #IMSA #Mazda'

b'For one last time, the #Mazda Soul Red Crystal and the Arctic White DPi sister cars will challenge side by side at @sebringraceway. \n\nToday #MazdaMotorsports will qualify for the #Sebring12. #IMSA'
b'It\xe2\x80\x99s a Top-3 finish for the Mazda RT24-P #77 and P7 for the #55. We\xe2\x80\x99ll be back on track tomorrow ready to push hard in qualifying. #MazdaMotorsports #Sebring12'

b'This weekend, #MazdaMotorsports takes on one final test of endurance this #IMSA season @sebringraceway. We\xe2\x80\x99re prepared to give it our all for the historic #Sebring12, starting with practice 1 at 10:05 AM ET. #NeverStopChallenging'

b'As we head back to @sebringraceway, we\xe2\x80\x99re reflecting on our time at this historic venue earlier this summer. Download high resolution versions of a few of our favorite #MazdaMotorsports photos via link in bio. #Mazda #IMSA'

b'Congratulations to #SpecMX5 National Champion, @justinpiscitellracing, and to all of the podium finishers and scholarship prize winners from this past weekend\xe2\x80\x99s championship races. Such a large field of talented drivers and close podium finishes have made this season thrilling to watch. #MazdaMotorsports'

b'Don\xe2\x80\x99t forget to tune in today for the Spec MX-5 National Championship. Race 1 will be live-streamed with corner cameras and commentators on the SVRA Facebook page at 4:40 PM ET. You can follow live scoring for tomorrow\xe2\x80\x99s race at 11:30 AM on the SVRA app. We wish the best of luck to all of the #SpecMX5 drivers competing today. #MazdaMotorsports'
b'#TBT to the Mazda Soul Red Crystal and the Arctic White careening down the corkscrew at @weathertechraceway. #MazdaMotorsports'

b'The Spec MX-5 National Championship will be live-streamed this weekend with corner cameras and commentators at https://www.facebook.com/svralife. \n\nThere\xe2\x80\x99s 70K in total #Mazda scholarships on the line for drivers. Tune in this Saturday at 4:40 PM ET for race 1, and 11:30 AM ET Sunday for race 2 to catch all the action. #MazdaMotorsports #SpecMX5'

b'It\xe2\x80\x99s a solid finish for #MazdaMotorsports with the Mazda RT24-P #55 coming home in fourth and the #77 in fifth to end our time at @weathertechraceway. The team will be back for one final endurance challenge on November 14th at @sebringraceway. #IMSA'

b"It's a compact day on track at @weathertechraceway, with qualifying at 9:20 AM PT, followed by the 2 hr 40 min Monterey Sports Car Championship race. You can follow along with #MazdaMotorsports on IMSA radio at 1:00 PM PT. #IMSAMonterey"

b'The #77 is fastest in practice 2 and the #55 is 3rd to round out opening day at @WeatherTechRaceway. #MazdaMotorsports will qualify tomorrow at 9:20 AM PT before the Monterey Sports Car Championship race begins at 1:00 PM PT. #IMSAMonterey'

b'A steadfast belief in our #PowerofPotential continues to be the driving force behind #MazdaMotorsports. The team is fully prepared for the penultimate event of the season @weathertechraceway, starting with two practice sessions today at 8:00 AM and 12:15 PM PT.'
b'The #IMSA race season is winding down, but we\xe2\x80\x99re not done yet. This weekend, the #MazdaMotorsports team heads to @weathertechraceway for the final sprint race of 2020.'

b"The 2020 race seasons are already coming to a close. For this #WallpaperWednesday, we're looking back at the final #MX5Cup race at @gpstpete and #motulpetitlemans with the sister DPi cars at @roadatlanta. Head to our stories to screenshot your favorites."

b'After a full season of racing, 1 or 2 positions on track in the final race made the difference in clinching a championship title, proving how competitive the Global Mazda MX-5 Cup series is. \n\nTom Long dives into the exciting finale in his latest blog. Link in bio. #MazdaMotorsports #MX5Cup'

b'In true Mazda never-give-up spirit, @michael_carter08 pushed hard and drove with heart to clinch the Global Mazda MX-5 Cup championship title. He now joins an illustrious list of drivers who have had their professional racing careers launched through the #MX5Cup series. #MazdaMotorsports'

b'The #MX5Cup finale at the Grand Prix of St. Petersburg perfectly reflected the 2020 season, showcasing intense competition. The entire field of drivers overcame challenges in an unconventional season, unleashing their potential in sports car racing. Congratulations to today\xe2\x80\x99s podium finishers, and to the 2020 Global Mazda MX-5 Cup champion, @michael_carter08. #MazdaMotorsports'

b'It\xe2\x80\x99s the final race day for #MX5Cup, and it\xe2\x80\x99s going to be an action-packed finale. Be sure to tune in today as we name a new Global Mazda MX-5 Cup champion. Tune in to follow live: link in bio. #MazdaMotorsports'

b'@greshamwagner is the provisional polesitter for tomorrow morning\xe2\x80\x99s race. With just two races left, @michael_carter08 leads @robertnoaker by only seven points in the overall standings. Tune in tomorrow at 8:30 AM ET as we begin the final showdown. #MazdaMotorsports'

b'As we head into the final race weekend of the 2020 #MX5Cup season, this talented field of drivers will take to the streets of @GPStPete as the championship challengers focus on the prize: a championship title and a scholarship valued at $200,000 that will advance the career of an aspiring driver. #MazdaMotorsports'

b'It\xe2\x80\x99s been a thrilling #MX5Cup season with final lap battles, first-time wins, repeat venues and all new tracks. Now it all comes down to this: the final fight for the championship on the Streets of St. Petersburg. It all starts tomorrow at 9 AM ET. #MazdaMotorsports'

b'Congratulations to all nominees for the 2020 MX-5 Cup Shootout. Drivers from varying backgrounds in amateur sports car racing will compete Nov. 16-17 at @RoadAtlanta. The winner will receive a $110K scholarship for the 2021 @GlobalMX5Cup season, & their car will sport Mazda\xe2\x80\x99s Soul Red Crystal throughout the season. #MazdaMotorsports Read more via link in bio'
b'No matter what obstacles we face, Mazda\xe2\x80\x99s #ChallengerSpirit always remains. On to Laguna Seca. #MazdaMotorsports'

b'It was a formidable effort on the part of the drivers, engineers & crew to overcome today\xe2\x80\x99s challenges & get both cars to the finish line at #MotulPetitLeMans. The #55 comes home 6th & #77 in 7th. With that, we look ahead to the Monterey Sports Car Championship. #MazdaMotorsports'
b'Everyone in the #MazdaMotorsports program has come to @roadatlanta with one goal in mind: to bring home a victory at #MotulPetitLeMans. Tune in to NBC Sports at 12:30 PM ET.'

b'The entire #MazdaMotorsports team is ready to dig deep and rise to the challenge of tomorrow\xe2\x80\x99s 10-hour test of endurance. The Mazda RT24-P #55 will roll off 4th and the #77 6th to begin #MotulPetitLeMans.'
b'It\xe2\x80\x99s a quick day of qualifying at @roadatlanta. Follow live timing and scoring at scoring.imsa.com as the Mazda RT24-P #77 and #55 hit the track at 1:20 PM ET. #MazdaMotorsports'

b'It\xe2\x80\x99s P5 and P6 for the Mazda RT24-P #55 and #77 respectively to wrap up a solid opening day of practice at @roadatlanta. We\xe2\x80\x99ll be back on track tomorrow at 1:20 PM ET for qualifying. #MazdaMotorsports'

b'We\xe2\x80\x99re excited to announce that the @GlobalMX5Cup will join @imsa_racing for the 2021 season. In IMSA, we have a sanctioning partner who shares Mazda\xe2\x80\x99s same commitment to uplifting people through the energy and excitement of sportscar racing. #MazdaMotorsports #MX5Cup'

b'Teamwork, dedication and human ingenuity are at the heart of #MazdaMotorsports, and it will take all of these elements to master the 10-hour endurance race this weekend at Road Atlanta. The sister Mazda DPi cars will hit the track today for 3 practice sessions, beginning at 11:15 AM ET.'

b'Do you know a local hero? #MazdaMotorsports is excited to share @mazdausa\xe2\x80\x99s program #MazdaHeroes, which will recognize those that selflessly give back to their communities. Fifty people will be featured and rewarded with a #Mazda MX-5 Miata 100th Anniversary Special Edition as the company\xe2\x80\x99s way of saying \xe2\x80\x9cthank you.\xe2\x80\x9d To nominate by Oct. 25, visit www.MazdaUSA.com/Mazda-heroes.'

b'There\xe2\x80\x99s nothing quite like the thrill of a victory lap or a podium finish at the SCCA National Championship Runoffs. #Mazda racers showed their heart and skills out on track all weekend long at @roadamerica. #SCCARunoffs #MazdaMotorsports'

b'This weekend saw the closest finish in #MX5Cup history when rookie @jaredthomasracing earned his 1st victory by just 0.0009-second over @greshamwagner. Wagner went on to bring home a win in race 2 at @njmotorsportspark. @GlobalMX5Cup will be back on track at St. Pete for the final two rounds. #MazdaMotorsports'

b'Several national champions were crowned this weekend, & a total of 22 #Mazda racers earned a spot on the podium at the #SCCARunoffs. Rookie Jared Thomas win his 1st #MX5Cup race by fractions of a second, & Gresham Wagner had a strong victory in race 2. Congratulations, drivers. #MazdaMotorsports'

b'It\xe2\x80\x99s race day for #Mazda drivers across the U.S. With only a few races remaining at the #SCCARunoffs, we\xe2\x80\x99ll be cheering for more #Mazda racers to claim a national title. #MX5Cup also gets closer to the final stretch with rounds 9 & 10 of the series championship. Follow along with #MazdaMotorsports all day long.'

b'It\xe2\x80\x99s been an action-packed weekend watching #Mazda racers give it their all out on track. So far 15 drivers have claimed a spot on the podium in Mazda race cars at the #SCCARunoffs. We\xe2\x80\x99ve got one more day of racing, starting at 8:15 AM CT tomorrow morning. #MazdaMotorsports'

b'More than 200 Mazdas and Mazda-powered race cars will hit the track this weekend between the SCCA Runoffs at @roadamerica, Global Mazda MX-5 Cup at @njmotorsportspark, and @specmx5 at @racesonoma. We hope #MazdaMotorsports fans are ready to enjoy a weekend full of racing passion and on-track thrills.'

b'Winning an SCCA National Championship title is a bucket list item for road racers, and several #Mazda racers achieved that goal today. Congratulations to all 10 of today\xe2\x80\x99s podium finishers. We\xe2\x80\x99ll be back on track tomorrow to enjoy more #SCCARunoffs and #MX5Cup.'

b'Are you ready for the 57th running of the most prestigious amateur road racing event in the U.S? The best regional racers throughout the country will go head-to-head today at the #SCCARunoffs. Follow along via #MazdaMotorsports to cheer on our many Mazda racers. Watch live via #linkinbio'

b'It\xe2\x80\x99s been a great showing so far for #MazdaMotorsports on the final day of qualifying at the #SCCARunoffs. Mazda comprises 11 of 12 entries of the new Formula X class, and 18 of 32 in the STL class, both of which qualified this morning. 2019 #SCCARunoffs National Champion and Mazda racer Danny Steyn took pole in the STL class after the 3 qualifying days. Great job today to all #Mazda racers.'

b'This week at Road America, more than 180 Mazdas and Mazda-powered race cars will compete for the ultimate prize in club racing: a national championship at the #SCCARunoffs. #MazdaMotorsports will provide support to Mazda racers all week, and anticipates an exciting race weekend.'

b'\xe2\x80\x9cNow that the #MX5Cup season is past its halfway point, the mental focus shifts a bit for drivers & teams as the championship points picture becomes more clear.\xe2\x80\x9d \n\n@tomlongracing shares his insights as @globalmx5cup heads to @njmotorsportspark this weekend. #LinkInBio #MazdaMotorsports'
b'For this #TBT, we\xe2\x80\x99re reflecting on the teamwork, dedication, and ingenuity that powered us to a 2nd place finish at the #Rolex24 earlier this year. #MazdaMotorsports'

b'This #WallpaperWednesday, we\xe2\x80\x99re admiring the way #MazdaMotorsports cars look out on the @officialmidohio track. You can download high resolution shots of the #Mazda RT24-Ps and #MX5Cup cars via link in bio.'

b'Automotive YouTuber @caseyputsch reviews his first drive at speed in a @globalmx5cup car prepared by @flis.performance at @officialmidohio. Check out the full video on YouTube and get his take on why the #MX5Cup car is not only fun to drive, but also one of the best values in racing. Link in Bio.'

b'After a day full of challenges out on track, the Mazda RT24-P #55 ultimately came in fourth and the #77 in fifth to finish to out #MazdaMotorsports\xe2\x80\x99 weekend at @officialmidohio. The DPi cars will return at @roadatlanta on October 15th. #IMSA'

b'It\xe2\x80\x99s race day for the WeatherTech Sports Car Challenge, and our final day on track after a weekend full of racing at Mid-Ohio. Qualifying is up first at 8:50 AM ET. Then tune in to TrackPass on NBC Sports at 2:00 PM for the Sports Car Challenge at Mid-Ohio. #MazdaMotorsports'

b'The #Mazda RT24-Ps ended their final practice with the #55 in 5th and the #77 in 6th. We\xe2\x80\x99ll be back on track tomorrow morning for qualifying at 8:50 AM ET, followed by the 2 hour and 40 minute Sports Car Challenge at Mid-Ohio. #MazdaMotorsports'

b'In another eventful #MX5Cup race finale, @michael_carter08 takes home the win for Round 8. With @selinrollan in second and @jaredthomasracing in third, the podium full of #MRT24 scholarship winners reflects #MazdaMotorsports\xe2\x80\x99 history of supporting talented drivers.'

b'From drivers just starting their racing journey to those at the pinnacle of the sport, all Mazda racers are joined together by their joy of driving and competition. This weekend, we follow the journey of the #MX5Cup and Mazda RT24-P drivers as they all get to live their shared passion on the same track.'

b'@robertnoaker wins Round 7 at @officialmidohio, making it his 6th career win in #MX5Cup and 3rd win of the year. He\xe2\x80\x99ll share the front row for tomorrow morning\xe2\x80\x99s race with @michael_carter08. We\xe2\x80\x99ll be back on track at 8:50 AM ET for @globalmx5cup Race 2. #MazdaMotorsports'

b'#MazdaMotorsports\xe2\x80\x99 love and enthusiasm for sports car racing will be on full display this weekend, with three consecutive race days at @officialmidohio. We invite you to follow along as we bring you all the @globalmx5cup and @imsa_racing action. #IMSA #MX5Cup'

b'Maximizing your race craft is essential in executing a successful race weekend. With one @officialmidohio weekend already under their belts this season, @GlobalMX5Cup drivers have a unique opportunity to put their learnings to the test at the circuit once more. #MazdaMotorsports #MX5Cup'

b'Before we head into another exciting race weekend at @officialmidohio, we\xe2\x80\x99re taking it back to 2019 @imsa_racing Mid-Ohio Sports Car Challenge for this #WallpaperWednesday. Head over to stories to screenshot your favorites. #MazdaMotorsports'

b'Every Mazda is engineered to celebrate the joy of driving. The same attention to detail that went into the Mazda RT24-P can be found in @mazdausa road cars, giving you a comfortable and joyful driving experience every time. #MazdaMotorsports'
b'Are you a Mazda racer? We\xe2\x80\x99re always looking to feature drivers that enjoy racing as part of the #MazdaMotorsports family. Tag us and share your story!'
b'#TBT Join Jonathan Bomarito as he maneuvers through the challenging twists and turns of @roadatlanta during the #TireRackGrandPrix. #MazdaMotorsports #IMSA'

b'After buying his first Mazda MX-5 race car, @grantwestracing was instantly hooked. From quick success in NASA time trial events to finishing 2nd overall in the NASA SE Championship, he now competes in the Spec MX-5 Challenge series, where he\xe2\x80\x99s already seen a win and 6 podium finishes. #GrassrootsTuesday #MazdaMotorsports'

b'From @greshamwagner leading every lap of Race 1, to @michael_carter08\xe2\x80\x99s bold move earning him a win in the final lap of Race 2, @officialmidohio had no shortage of significant moments. Two podiums keeps @robertnoaker in the championship lead. We\xe2\x80\x99ll be back in 2 weeks time for both #MX5Cup & #IMSA races.'

b'An incredible show of racing this weekend, with exactly the type of exciting finish we\xe2\x80\x99ve come to expect from @globalmx5cup in round 6. Congratulations to @greshamwagner, @michael_carter08 and @robertnoaker, who dominated the #MX5Cup podium this weekend. #MazdaMotorsports'

b"It's still anyone's championship to win as we head into @globalmx5cup Rounds 5 and 6. Spectators will join us for an exciting race day at @officialmidohio. Follow #MazdaMotorsports Instagram stories and watch the live feed via #LinkInBio. #MX5Cup"
b'The grid is set and @greshamwagner will lead the pack for #MX5Cup Round 5. The @officialmidohio @globalmx5cup action all starts tomorrow morning with Race 1 at 9:25 AM ET. #MazdaMotorsports'

b'More than half-a-million dollars in prizes are on the line this @globalmx5cup season, including the $200,000 scholarship for the Global Mazda MX-5 Cup champion. These #MX5Cup prizes can help springboard drivers into a career in sports car racing. Follow along all weekend at @officialmidohio on #MazdaMotorsports Instagram stories.'

b'Looking to join us in celebrating a podium finish at @roadatlanta? Now you can relive the moment with high resolution #MazdaMotorsports wallpapers. Download your favorites and format to any device via the link in bio. #IMSA'

b'How about a lap around @IndianapolisMotorSpeedway in an #MX5Cup car to wake up your senses this Monday? Hop on board with @jackson_robillard and ride around the famed Brickyard. @mccumbeemcaleerracing'

b'No other brand in North America does as much to get drivers off the sidelines and behind the wheel as #MazdaMotorsports. It\xe2\x80\x99s been a weekend full of strong competition, lessons learned, and passionate racing. #IMSA #MX5Cup'

b'Even in the face of adversity, we will #NeverStopChallenging. A great effort by the team to earn a second place finish for the Mazda RT24-P #55. A brake issue ended the race early for the #77, but the #MazdaMotorsports @multimaticmotorsports crew will keep pushing and look forward to @officialmidohio.'

b'We\xe2\x80\x99ll be ready for the green flag to fly at 11:35 AM ET over one of America\xe2\x80\x99s best road courses, @RoadAtlanta. @ryanhunterreay and @olivierplaracing join our full-season drivers as we take on the #TireRackGrandPrix, airing on NBCSN. #MazdaMotorsports #IMSA'

b'The Mazda RT24-P #77 and the #55 will roll off 4th and 5th, respectively, for tomorrow\xe2\x80\x99s race. Consistency will be key for the six hour test of endurance at @Roadatlanta, which airs tomorrow at 11:30 AM ET on NBCSN. #MazdaMotorsports #IMSA'

b'The Battery Tender:registered: Global Mazda MX-5 Cup race day had no shortage of close-fought battles right up until the end. Congratulations to @selinrollan, @toddspeed and all of today\xe2\x80\x99s #MX5Cup podium finishers. #MazdaMotorsports'

b'More Mazdas are road raced on any given weekend in the U.S. than any other brand. \n\nYou\xe2\x80\x99ll see that in full force this weekend as we follow @globalmx5cup at @indianapolismotorspeedway & @imsa_racing at @roadatlanta. First up: #MX5Cup Race 1 at 8:45 AM ET.  #MazdaMotorsports #IMSA'

b'Day one at @indianapolismotorspeedway is complete, but we\xe2\x80\x99ve got plenty more #MazdaMotorsports action coming up this weekend. Tomorrow we\xe2\x80\x99ll follow along with both @globalmx5cup races, plus we\xe2\x80\x99ll join the Mazda RT24-P sister cars for an @imsa_racing weekend at @roadatlanta. Stay tuned.'

b'For the first time since 2017, @indianapolismotorspeedway will be the stage for a large and talented field of @GlobalMX5Cup drivers as we ready for Rounds 3 & 4. Practice 1 begins at 8:45 AM ET, and you can follow along on #MazdaMotorsports Instagram stories, and through the link in bio.'

b'At just 16 years old, Robert Noaker is leading the 2020 @globalmx5cup series after the first event. The Mazda racer is the youngest race winner in IndyCar-sanctioned history, and we\xe2\x80\x99ll see him back in action this Thursday at @indianapolismotorspeedway. \n\xe2\x80\xa2\xe2\x80\xa2\xe2\x80\xa2\n#GrassrootsTuesday #MX5Cup #MazdaMotorsports'
b'#MondayMotivation: Never Give Up. Never Stop Challenging. \n\nThis decal may be nearly 30 years old, but the same #Mazda principles still apply today. #MazdaMotorsports'

b'It\xe2\x80\x99s been a few years since @globalmx5cup has been at @indianapolismotorspeedway, so today we\xe2\x80\x99re throwing it back to 2017, the last time #MX5Cup took place at the Indianapolis road course. We\xe2\x80\x99ll see you there next week. #TBT #MazdaMotorsports'

b'There\xe2\x80\x99s something striking about the way the light dances off of the Mazda Soul Red Crystal of the #55 & the Arctic White #77. Which is your favorite? You can download these #WallpaperWednesday shots through the link in our Instagram Story.'

b"Hannah Grisham is a Mazda racer with several championships under her belt. She\xe2\x80\x99s a 2019 NASA So-Cal Spec Miata and TMC champion, and we're excited to see what's in store for the rest of her 2020 season. #GrassrootsTuesday #MazdaMotorsports #SpecMiata"
b'Whether you\xe2\x80\x99re flying around a corner at Road America, or simply cruising in your road car, the joy and love of driving a #Mazda remains the same. #MazdaMonday #MazdaMotorsports'

b'Take a 360 degree look inside the 1991 Mazda RX-7 IMSA GTO driven by Jeremy Barnes during the 2015 #RolexReunion. You can control your view over on our YouTube channel: Link in Bio #TBT #MazdaMotorsports'

b'For this #GrassrootsTuesday, we\xe2\x80\x99d like to congratulate all the Spec MX-5 Challenge Series Round 3 podium finishers from this past weekend at Road America. Are you a Mazda Grassroots racer? Tag us and tell us about your journey. #MazdaMotorsports #Mazda #SpecMX5'
b'The Mazda RT24-P is a race car that\xe2\x80\x99s as beautiful as it is fast, and the ultimate embodiment of @mazdausa\xe2\x80\x99s KODO-Soul of Motion design philosophy. #MazdaMotorsports #IMSA'
b'Come along for a #TBT ride on board with @olivierplaracing in the Mazda RT24-P #77 as he set the unofficial course record at @disupdates. #MazdaMotorsports #IMSA'
b'This #WallpaperWednesday, relive our 1-2 victory at #WeatherTech240. \n\nNow you can download high resolution versions of some of our favorite images. Link in bio. #MazdaMotorsports'

b"\xe2\x80\x9cMazda has a rich history of being at the forefront of sports car racing, and truly supports grassroots drivers unlike any other. The support and belief that Mazda has shown me has given me the spark I've needed to continue to make this dream a reality.\xe2\x80\x9d - Bryce Cornet. #MazdaMotorsports #Mazda #grassrootstuesday"

b'Central to everything we do at #Mazda is one simple thought: \xe2\x80\x9cBy humans, for humans.\xe2\x80\x9d It takes a lot of manpower and human ingenuity to keep #MazdaMotorsports running, and we\xe2\x80\x99re grateful for every hardworking engineer, driver and crew member. #IMSA'

b"For this #TBT, we conclude our two week stretch at Road America. From a memorable #MX5Cup season opener to a strong battle fought at the front of the #IMSA field, there was no shortage of excitement at America's National Park of Speed. \r\n\r\n#MazdaMotorsports"
